5 HUNDO HAS FALLEN 🚨 broke into the 500lbs bench press club with 507lbs (1lb clips each side) ending the prep with 22lbs bench press PR. Now to taper until meet day

I waited 6 years to post this 😂 

First 500 bench - 507lbs ✔️ 2023 
First 400 bench - 415lbs ✔️ 2018 
First 300 bench - 315 ✔️ 2017 

Basically stalled for 2 years because I didn’t know how to bench LOL but worked on my form and technique a lot. 600 next 😤

Prep is officially over. The easy part is done, now the real challenge is putting it all together on meet day where it matters. Been a year since I stepped foot on a platform and spent 6 months this year injured where I couldn’t even drive or sleep without pain. Successfully broke my last meet total by 129lbs. 

Squats went crazy this prep, I rarely did my backdowns but I kept up with my accessories and went from 733 pre injury max to 785 post injury max. 52lbs PR.

Bench also surprised me a lot, going from 485 to 507lbs the most I’ve put on my bench in any prep. I’d usually be lucky to add 10lbs at the end of a prep. 

Deadlifts I’m happy with, as just back in April-may I couldn’t even pull 500 pain free, broke my pre injury PR by 15lbs while fatigued. Going from 850 to 865. 

Truth is I wasn’t able to do this without help from others, if I forgot to mention you or tag you, I’m sorry 😇 

#benchpress #powerlifting #deadlift #gym #motiv

Not much of a meet recap but it is 

Squats: 
1- 712lbs ✅✅✅
2- 756 ✅✅✅ 23lbs meet PR and left around 15lbs more in the tank 
3- scratched third for deadlifts

Bench press: 
1-469 ✅✅✅
2- 500lbs ❌✅❌ left foot slipped on the way up surprised I locked it out but unfortunately it didn’t pass. 

As for deadlifts, warmups were good until I got to my last warmup, felt a sharp pull in my right side/rear delt after I got it over my knees. Felt a sharp pain so I just took a token deadlift. Not sure how serious it is yet but will be able to tell within a couple days. You win some you lose some 🤷🏽‍♂️ just glad it’s over with tbh. 

Thanks to Seth Bowles for putting this meet together and investing out of his own pocket for the payouts.

Exorcising these demons, the saga continues.
